==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wombat
<hw>Wom"bat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the native name,
<ets>womback</ets>, <ets>wombach</ets>, in Australia.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of three species of Australian burrowing
marsupials of the genus <gen>Phascolomys</gen>, especially the common
species (<spn>Phascolomys ursinus</spn>). They are nocturnal in their
habits, and feed mostly on roots.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Womby</ent>⟦br⟧
